# Public vs Private Documentation

This is a **public open-source repo**. Anything committed must make sense to strangers who clone without your private files.

**Supported vs roadmap wording** within public docs is a separate concern — see [public-docs.mdc](./public-docs.mdc).

---

## Before adding or editing committed content (agents)

**Stop and classify first.** Do not draft into public files and relocate later.

Ask:

1. **Contributor or stranger?** — Would someone who cloned without your private files need this to build, test, or integrate?
2. **Maintainer ops?** — GitHub Settings click paths, branch protection checklists, post-merge admin todos, deploy hostnames, cron paths, funding/session notes?
3. **Product truth?** — Supported vs roadmap, API behavior, security controls contributors should know?

| If… | Put it in… |
|-----|------------|
| Yes to (1) or (3), generic | Public `docs/`, `README.md`, `CONTRIBUTING.md`, package READMEs, `THREAT_MODEL.md` |
| Yes to (2), or “my next steps after merge” | Gitignored `*.local.md` (any path — root or `docs/internal/`) |
| Workflow YAML | Behavior only in committed files; **no** Settings → Branches step lists in comments |
| PR template / CONTRIBUTING | Contributor checklist only — not maintainer admin runbooks |
| `docs/internal/README.md` | Convention only — **not** a private folder; do not list runbook topics or admin todos here |

**`docs/internal/` is not gitignored** — only `*.local.md` files are. When unsure: **private first**, distill a generic sentence into public docs if needed. Never link public docs to `*.local.md`.

---

## Public (committed)

| Location | Belongs here |
|----------|----------------|
| `README.md`, `CONTRIBUTING.md`, `AGENTS.md` | Project overview, contributor setup, agent pointers |
| `docs/PLAN.md`, `docs/SUPPORTED.md`, `docs/INTEGRATION.md` | Technical roadmap, support matrix, integration guides |
| `docs/deploy-eu.md`, `docs/deploy-cdn-examples.md` | **Provider-generic** deploy/CDN steps — no maintainer hostnames, IPs, or real cron paths |
| `FUNDING.md` | Sponsor-facing funding info only |
| `packages/*/README.md`, `THREAT_MODEL.md`, `SECURITY.md` | Package API, security policy |
| `.github/internal/wp/` | WP acceptance criteria (dev process — **not** secret; name means “not user-facing marketing”) |
| `docs/internal/README.md` | **Only** committed file under `docs/internal/` — explains the `*.local.md` convention (no runbook topics or admin steps) |

Public docs must be **self-contained**. Do not link to or reference gitignored `*.local.md` files.

---

## Private (gitignored — may exist locally)

Root `.gitignore` excludes optional local files. **Do not commit these.** Most contributors will not have them.

| Pattern | Typical use (project lead only) |
|---------|--------------------------------|
| `*.local.md`, `*.local.txt` | Private runbooks, session notes |
| `PLAN.local.md` | Funding/session bootstrap |
| `docs/internal/<topic>.local.md` | Ops runbooks with real hostnames and cutover detail |
| `scripts/deploy.sh`, `scripts/provision-server.sh`, `scripts/provision-base.conf` | Server-specific deploy |
| `.env` | Secrets — use a password manager, not git |

Distill generic guidance into public `docs/`; keep host-specific detail in gitignored files or off-repo.

---

## Never put in public (committed) files

- Grant applications, funding strategy, compliance correspondence, monetary amounts
- Maintainer ops runbooks, GitHub admin checklists (branch protection, org settings), production hostnames, origin IPs, SSH aliases, real cron paths
- “After you merge, do X in Settings” reminders in `CONTRIBUTING.md`, PR templates, or workflow comment blocks
- API keys, tokens, `.env` values, or pointers that expose secrets
- Links to `*.local.md` files (absent for other clones)
- New committed `docs/internal/*.md` beyond `docs/internal/README.md`
- Unevaluated third-party AI/agent tool endorsements in `README.md`, `docs/*`, or package READMEs

---

## Boundary examples

| Private (gitignored) | Public (`docs/`) |
|----------------------|------------------|
| Production DNS cutover, apex hostname removal | Generic CDN pull-zone + `/api/*` cache bypass |
| Firewall/cron with real paths on a named host | Generic install/refresh script usage |
| Funding amounts, legal entity setup | `FUNDING.md` (sponsor-facing) |
| `scripts/deploy.sh` with server host | `docs/deploy-eu.md` |
| GitHub branch protection / post-merge admin checklist | Any gitignored `*.local.md` (not under a “private” folder — the path is public until gitignored by name) |
